pins.title: Willis Tower (Sears Tower) — Chicago's Iconic Bundled-Tube Skyscraper
pins.description: The Willis Tower by Fazlur Khan (1973) was once the world's tallest building. Its revolutionary bundled-tube design redefined skyscraper engineering in the Windy City. #architecture #chicago #skyscraper #willistower #modernism #chicagoarchitecture

pins.title: 860-880 Lake Shore Drive — Mies van der Rohe's Glass Towers
pins.description: Mies van der Rohe's 1951 Lake Shore Drive apartments revolutionized residential architecture with their minimalist glass-and-steel curtain walls. A defining moment in International Style. #architecture #chicago #miesvanderrohe #modernism #internationalstyle

pins.title: Art Institute of Chicago — Beaux-Arts Masterpiece on Michigan Avenue
pins.description: The Art Institute of Chicago (1893) blends Beaux-Arts grandeur with Renzo Piano's 2009 Modern Wing. One of the world's great museums in an architectural landmark. #architecture #chicago #beauxarts #artinstitute #museum #chicagoarchitecture

pins.title: John Hancock Center — SOM's X-Braced Tower on Michigan Avenue
pins.description: The John Hancock Center (1969) by SOM features an iconic X-braced exterior structure. At 100 stories, its bold engineering made it a Chicago landmark. #architecture #chicago #skyscraper #som #modernism #hightech

pins.title: Rookery Building — Chicago School Landmark by Burnham & Root
pins.description: The Rookery (1888) by Burnham & Root is a Chicago School masterpiece with a stunning light court later redesigned by Frank Lloyd Wright. Historic architecture at its finest. #architecture #chicago #chicagoschool #burnhamandroot #historicbuildings

pins.title: Wrigley Building — Gleaming White Terra Cotta on the Magnificent Mile
pins.description: The Wrigley Building (1924) dazzles with its white terra-cotta facade on the Magnificent Mile. A stunning example of Chicago's Beaux-Arts commercial architecture. #architecture #chicago #beauxarts #magnificentmile #chicagoarchitecture

pins.title: Marina City — Bertrand Goldberg's Iconic Corncob Towers
pins.description: Marina City (1964) by Bertrand Goldberg — the iconic "corncob" towers that pioneered mixed-use urban living along the Chicago River. Bold, sculptural, unforgettable. #architecture #chicago #brutalism #marinacity #modernism #iconicbuildings

pins.title: Aqua Tower — Jeanne Gang's Undulating Skyscraper
pins.description: The Aqua Tower (2009) by Jeanne Gang features rippling concrete balconies that create a stunning wave-like facade. One of the 21st century's most celebrated buildings. #architecture #chicago #contemporary #aquatower #jeannegang #skyscraper

pins.title: Chicago Cultural Center — Home of the World's Largest Tiffany Dome
pins.description: The Chicago Cultural Center houses the world's largest Tiffany stained-glass dome. This Beaux-Arts gem is a free cultural landmark in the heart of downtown. #architecture #chicago #beauxarts #tiffany #culturalcenter #historicbuildings

pins.title: Grote Kerk — Medieval Gothic Church in The Hague

pins.description: Noordeinde 29 features a striking Art Deco facade with geometric elegance and stylized details on one of The Hague's most prestigious streets. #architecture #thehague #denhaag #artdeco #noordeinde #dutch

pins.description: Veenkade features charming canal-side architecture with traditional Dutch facades reflected in the water — quintessential Hague living. #architecture #thehague #denhaag #canal #dutch #traditional

pins.description: Plesmanweg showcases bold contemporary architecture with innovative Dutch design along one of The Hague's modern corridors. #architecture #thehague #denhaag #contemporary #dutch #innovative

pins.description: Frederikstraat in the Zeeheldenkwartier features charming Dutch residential architecture with period details and warm brick facades. #architecture #thehague #denhaag #zeeheldenkwartier #dutch #charm

pins.description: Pr. Beatrixlaan features sleek modern architecture with glass towers and innovative design in The Hague's evolving skyline. #architecture #thehague #denhaag #modern #glass #skyline

pins.description: Plesmanweg features modern Dutch office architecture with clean lines and functional design along The Hague's business corridors. #architecture #thehague #denhaag #office #modern #functional

pins.description: This Denver bungalow on S Emerson exemplifies the Arts & Crafts movement with natural materials, wide eaves, and Colorado mountain-inspired design. #architecture #denver #colorado #craftsman #bungalow #artsandcrafts

pins.description: This S Vine Street home showcases Denver's diverse residential architecture with period details reflecting Colorado's building heritage. #architecture #denver #colorado #historic #residential #denverarchitecture

pins.title: N Marion Street — Victorian Denver Residence
pins.description: This N Marion Street home in Capitol Hill showcases Denver's Victorian residential heritage with ornate woodwork and classic Colorado design. #architecture #denver #colorado #victorian #capitolhill #historic

pins.title: Denver Union Station — Beaux-Arts Transportation Landmark
pins.description: Denver Union Station (1914) is a stunning Beaux-Arts transportation landmark with terra cotta details and an iconic clock tower. Now a vibrant transit hub & hotel. #architecture #denver #colorado #beauxarts #unionstation #landmark

pins.title: Pearl Street Victorian — Capitol Hill Denver
pins.description: Pearl Street in Capitol Hill features some of Denver's finest Victorian homes with intricate woodwork and colorful facades. #architecture #denver #colorado #victorian #capitolhill #denverarchitecture

pins.title: 955 Pearl Street — Victorian Gem in Capitol Hill Denver
pins.description: This Pearl Street Victorian in Capitol Hill is a beautifully preserved example of Denver's 1880s residential architecture with ornate trim and classic design. #architecture #denver #colorado #victorian #capitolhill #historic

pins.title: 1209 Pennsylvania St — Denver Victorian Architecture
pins.description: This Pennsylvania Street home showcases Denver's Victorian residential architecture with elegant proportions and period craftsmanship. #architecture #denver #colorado #victorian #residential #denverarchitecture

pins.title: 1302 E 11th Ave — Capitol Hill Residential Architecture
pins.description: E 11th Avenue in Capitol Hill features Denver's diverse residential architecture with Victorian and Craftsman influences reflecting the neighborhood's heritage. #architecture #denver #colorado #capitolhill #residential #craftsman

pins.description: Corona Street in Denver features charming residential architecture with Arts & Crafts details and the warm character of Capitol Hill's historic homes. #architecture #denver #colorado #artsandcrafts #residential #historic

pins.title: 930 N Downing St — Denver's Architectural Heritage
pins.description: N Downing Street showcases Denver's rich architectural mix with historic homes reflecting the city's Victorian and early 20th-century building traditions. #architecture #denver #colorado #historic #residential #denverarchitecture

pins.title: Denver Museum of Nature & Science — City Park Landmark
pins.description: The Denver Museum of Nature & Science in City Park is a beloved civic landmark combining Neoclassical design with modern expansions. #architecture #denver #colorado #museum #neoclassical #citypark

pins.title: 420 E 11th Ave — Capitol Hill Denver Architecture
pins.description: This E 11th Avenue building in Capitol Hill represents Denver's vibrant architectural landscape where Victorian meets modern in Colorado's capital. #architecture #denver #colorado #capitolhill #mixed #denverarchitecture

pins.title: Bradish Johnson House — Second Empire Masterpiece in New Orleans
pins.description: The Bradish Johnson House (1872) on Prytania St features a rare mansard roof designed by James Freret. Now the McGehee School, it's a Garden District treasure. #architecture #neworleans #nola #secondempire #gardendistrict #historic

pins.title: Pitot House — French Colonial Creole Cottage on Bayou St. John
pins.description: The Pitot House (1799) is the only French Colonial Creole house open to the public in New Orleans — a raised cottage with West Indian influence on Moss Street. #architecture #neworleans #nola #frenchcolonial #creole #bayoustjohn

pins.title: Old U.S. Mint — Greek Revival Monument on Esplanade Avenue
pins.description: The Old U.S. Mint (1838) by William Strickland is the only mint to produce both US and Confederate currency. A massive Greek Revival landmark in New Orleans. #architecture #neworleans #nola #greekrevival #historic #esplanade

pins.title: Saenger Theatre — Atmospheric Theater Masterpiece in New Orleans
pins.description: The Saenger Theatre (1927) recreates a starlit Italian courtyard with projected clouds on the ceiling. A stunning atmospheric theater on Canal Street. #architecture #neworleans #nola #artdeco #theater #canalstreet

pins.title: Shotgun House — New Orleans' Most Iconic Building Type
pins.description: The shotgun house is New Orleans' most important architectural contribution — narrow, deep homes with rooms in a line, adapted from Caribbean & West African traditions. #architecture #neworleans #nola #shotgunhouse #vernacular #creole

pins.title: Contemporary Arts Center — Adaptive Reuse in New Orleans
pins.description: The Contemporary Arts Center (1905/1990) transformed a K&B warehouse into one of the South's premier art spaces. Adaptive reuse at its best in the Warehouse District. #architecture #neworleans #nola #adaptivereuse #contemporary #warehousedistrict

pins.title: New Orleans Museum of Art — Beaux-Arts in City Park
pins.description: NOMA (1911) anchors City Park with Beaux-Arts classicism and world-class collections. A cultural treasure surrounded by live oaks and sculpture gardens. #architecture #neworleans #nola #beauxarts #museum #citypark

pins.title: St. Louis Cathedral — Iconic French Quarter Landmark
pins.description: St. Louis Cathedral (1794) on Jackson Square is the oldest continuously active cathedral in the US. A stunning blend of Spanish Colonial and French architectural influence. #architecture #neworleans #nola #cathedral #frenchquarter #jacksonsquare

pins.title: The Cabildo — Spanish Colonial Landmark on Jackson Square
pins.description: The Cabildo (1799) on Jackson Square is where the Louisiana Purchase was signed. A magnificent Spanish Colonial building and Louisiana State Museum. #architecture #neworleans #nola #spanishcolonial #jacksonsquare #historic

pins.title: Pontalba Buildings — America's First Luxury Apartments
pins.description: The Pontalba Buildings (1851) on Jackson Square introduced cast-iron galleries to New Orleans. America's oldest luxury apartments and an architectural icon. #architecture #neworleans #nola #castiron #frenchquarter #jacksonsquare

pins.title: Hotel Monteleone — Beaux-Arts Landmark on Royal Street
pins.description: The Hotel Monteleone (1886) on Royal Street is a Beaux-Arts landmark that hosted Faulkner, Hemingway, and Tennessee Williams. Literary history meets grand architecture. #architecture #neworleans #nola #beauxarts #royalstreet #hotel

pins.title: Preservation Hall — Humble Creole Cottage, World-Famous Jazz
pins.description: Preservation Hall occupies a humble Creole cottage from 1817 on St. Peter Street. Proof that great architecture doesn't always announce itself. #architecture #neworleans #nola #creole #frenchquarter #jazz

pins.title: Gallier Hall — Greek Revival Pinnacle on St. Charles Avenue
pins.description: Gallier Hall (1853) by James Gallier Sr. is the pinnacle of Greek Revival civic architecture in the South. Former New Orleans City Hall on grand St. Charles Avenue. #architecture #neworleans #nola #greekrevival #stcharles #civic

pins.title: Longue Vue House — Classical Revival Estate in New Orleans
pins.description: Longue Vue House (1942) is a Classical Revival estate with stunning gardens — a hidden gem offering a glimpse into mid-century New Orleans elegance and wealth. #architecture #neworleans #nola #classicalrevival #estate #gardens

pins.title: Empire State Building — Art Deco Icon of New York City
pins.description: The Empire State Building (1931) is the world's most famous skyscraper. Its Art Deco crown and spire define the NYC skyline and American architectural ambition. #architecture #nyc #newyork #artdeco #skyscraper #empirestatebuilding

pins.title: Chrysler Building — Art Deco's Finest Moment in Manhattan
pins.description: The Chrysler Building (1930) with its stainless steel crown and eagle gargoyles is widely considered the finest Art Deco skyscraper ever built. Pure NYC magic. #architecture #nyc #newyork #artdeco #chryslerbuilding #skyscraper #manhattan

pins.title: Flatiron Building — New York's Iconic Triangular Landmark
pins.description: The Flatiron Building (1902) at the intersection of Broadway and Fifth Avenue is one of NYC's most photographed buildings with its unique triangular Beaux-Arts form. #architecture #nyc #newyork #beauxarts #flatiron #landmark #manhattan

pins.title: Grand Central Terminal — Beaux-Arts Transportation Masterpiece
pins.description: Grand Central Terminal (1913) is a Beaux-Arts masterpiece with its celestial ceiling mural and grand concourse. One of the world's most beautiful train stations. #architecture #nyc #newyork #beauxarts #grandcentral #landmark

pins.title: Woolworth Building — Gothic Cathedral of Commerce in NYC
pins.description: The Woolworth Building (1913) was the world's tallest building and earned the nickname 'Cathedral of Commerce' for its ornate Gothic Revival terra-cotta facade. #architecture #nyc #newyork #gothicrevival #woolworth #skyscraper

pins.title: One World Trade Center — Symbol of Resilience in Lower Manhattan
pins.description: One World Trade Center (2014) rises 1,776 feet as America's tallest building — a gleaming symbol of New York's resilience and architectural ambition. #architecture #nyc #newyork #contemporary #oneworldtrade #skyscraper #lowermanhattan

pins.title: Solomon R. Guggenheim Museum — Frank Lloyd Wright's NYC Masterwork
pins.description: The Guggenheim Museum (1959) by Frank Lloyd Wright features a revolutionary spiral rotunda that changed museum architecture forever. An Upper East Side icon. #architecture #nyc #newyork #franklloydwright #guggenheim #museum #modernism

pins.title: Lever House — International Style Pioneer on Park Avenue
pins.description: Lever House (1952) by SOM pioneered the glass curtain wall skyscraper on Park Avenue. A defining moment in International Style architecture. #architecture #nyc #newyork #internationalstyle #leverhouse #modernism #parkavenue

pins.title: Seagram Building — Mies van der Rohe's Bronze Masterpiece
pins.description: The Seagram Building (1958) by Mies van der Rohe is the definitive International Style skyscraper — bronze and glass perfection with its iconic plaza on Park Avenue. #architecture #nyc #newyork #miesvanderrohe #seagram #internationalstyle

pins.title: St. Patrick's Cathedral — Gothic Revival Splendor in Midtown
pins.description: St. Patrick's Cathedral (1879) is America's largest decorated Gothic Revival church, its soaring spires contrasting with Midtown Manhattan's modern skyscrapers. #architecture #nyc #newyork #gothicrevival #cathedral #stpatricks

pins.title: 30 Rockefeller Plaza — Art Deco Centerpiece of Rockefeller Center
pins.description: 30 Rock (1933) is the Art Deco centerpiece of Rockefeller Center — one of the greatest urban complexes ever built and home to NBC's famous studios. #architecture #nyc #newyork #artdeco #rockefellercenter #30rock #midtown

pins.title: MetLife Building — Modernist Tower Over Grand Central
pins.description: The MetLife Building (1963, formerly Pan Am) looms over Grand Central Terminal as a massive International Style tower that reshaped the Park Avenue skyline. #architecture #nyc #newyork #modernism #metlife #parkavenue #midtown

pins.title: Hearst Tower — Norman Foster's Diagrid Masterpiece in NYC
pins.description: The Hearst Tower (2006) by Norman Foster features a striking diagrid steel structure rising from a 1928 Art Deco base — old meets new in stunning fashion. #architecture #nyc #newyork #normanfoster #hightech #diagrid #contemporary

pins.title: Brooklyn Bridge — Gothic Revival Engineering Marvel
pins.description: The Brooklyn Bridge (1883) with its Gothic stone towers and steel cables is an engineering marvel and one of America's most iconic structures. #architecture #nyc #newyork #gothicrevival #bridge #brooklynbridge #engineering

pins.title: New York Public Library — Beaux-Arts Monument on Fifth Avenue
pins.description: The New York Public Library (1911) on Fifth Avenue is a Beaux-Arts triumph with its iconic stone lions, grand reading room, and magnificent facade. #architecture #nyc #newyork #beauxarts #library #fifthavenue #landmark

pins.title: The Dakota — NYC's Most Famous Residential Building
pins.description: The Dakota (1884) on Central Park West is NYC's most storied residential building — Germanic Renaissance Revival architecture with a legendary history. #architecture #nyc #newyork #renaissance #thedakota #centralparkwest #residential

pins.title: Citigroup Center — Modernist Innovation with the Angled Top
pins.description: Citigroup Center (1977) is instantly recognizable by its distinctive 45-degree angled top and raised stilts — a bold modernist statement in Midtown Manhattan. #architecture #nyc #newyork #modernism #citigroupcenter #skyscraper #midtown

pins.title: Independence Hall — Birthplace of American Democracy
pins.description: Independence Hall (1753) in Philadelphia is where the Declaration of Independence and Constitution were signed. Georgian architecture that changed the world. #architecture #philadelphia #philly #georgian #independencehall #historic #democracy

pins.title: Philadelphia City Hall — French Second Empire Grandeur
pins.description: Philadelphia City Hall (1901) is the world's tallest masonry building, crowned by a 37-foot statue of William Penn. Extraordinary French Second Empire architecture. #architecture #philadelphia #philly #secondempire #cityhall #landmark

pins.title: PSFS Building — America's First International Style Skyscraper
pins.description: The PSFS Building (1932) pioneered International Style in America with its revolutionary steel-frame curtain wall design. A Philadelphia architectural milestone. #architecture #philadelphia #philly #internationalstyle #modernism #skyscraper

pins.title: 30th Street Station — Beaux-Arts Transportation Temple
pins.description: Philadelphia's 30th Street Station (1933) is a monumental Beaux-Arts temple to travel with soaring Corinthian columns and a grand concourse. #architecture #philadelphia #philly #beauxarts #trainstation #30thstreet #landmark

pins.title: Philadelphia Museum of Art — Neoclassical Icon on the Parkway
pins.description: The Philadelphia Museum of Art (1928) crowns the Benjamin Franklin Parkway with its Greek Revival temple form — yes, those are the Rocky Steps! #architecture #philadelphia #philly #neoclassical #museum #rockysteps #landmark

pins.title: Eastern State Penitentiary — Gothic Revival Prison Architecture

pins.title: Kimmel Center — Rafael Viñoly's Barrel-Vaulted Concert Hall
pins.description: The Kimmel Center (2001) by Rafael Viñoly features a stunning barrel-vaulted glass roof sheltering world-class performance spaces on the Avenue of the Arts. #architecture #philadelphia #philly #contemporary #kimmelcenter #concerthall

pins.title: Comcast Technology Center — Philadelphia's Tallest Tower
pins.description: The Comcast Technology Center (2018) by Foster + Partners is Philadelphia's tallest building at 1,121 feet, featuring a striking glass tower with a Four Seasons hotel. #architecture #philadelphia #philly #contemporary #skyscraper #foster

pins.title: One Liberty Place — Postmodern Skyscraper that Broke the Height Barrier
pins.description: One Liberty Place (1987) famously broke Philadelphia's gentleman's agreement to never build taller than City Hall. A bold postmodern tower that changed the skyline. #architecture #philadelphia #philly #postmodern #skyscraper #onelibertyplace

pins.title: Academy of Music — America's Oldest Grand Opera House

pins.title: Free Library of Philadelphia — Beaux-Arts Temple of Learning

pins.title: Wanamaker Building — Grand Department Store Architecture

pins.title: Barnes Foundation — Tod Williams & Billie Tsien's Modern Masterwork
pins.description: The Barnes Foundation (2012) by Tod Williams Billie Tsien houses one of the world's greatest art collections in an elegant contemporary building on the Parkway. #architecture #philadelphia #philly #contemporary #barnesfoundation #museum

pins.title: Cathedral Basilica of Saints Peter and Paul — Philadelphia's Grand Church

pins.title: Betsy Ross House — Colonial Architecture in Old City Philadelphia

pins.title: Christ Church — Georgian Gem Where America's Founders Worshipped
pins.description: Christ Church (1744) is a Georgian masterpiece where Washington, Franklin, and other Founders worshipped. Its steeple was once the tallest structure in North America. #architecture #philadelphia #philly #georgian #christchurch #colonial #founders

pins.title: Franklin Institute — Art Deco Science Museum in Philadelphia
pins.description: The Franklin Institute (1934) is a grand Art Deco science museum on the Benjamin Franklin Parkway, featuring a massive marble rotunda and memorial hall. #architecture #philadelphia #philly #artdeco #franklininstitute #museum #science

pins.title: Transamerica Pyramid — San Francisco's Futurist Icon
pins.description: The Transamerica Pyramid (1972) by William Pereira is San Francisco's most iconic skyscraper — a bold futurist statement rising above the Financial District. #architecture #sanfrancisco #sf #transamericapyramid #futurism #skyscraper

pins.title: Painted Ladies — Victorian Row Houses at Alamo Square
pins.description: The Painted Ladies on Steiner Street are San Francisco's most photographed homes — colorful Queen Anne Victorians framing the city skyline at Alamo Square. #architecture #sanfrancisco #sf #victorian #paintedladies #alamosquare #queenanne

pins.title: SFMOMA — Mario Botta Meets Snøhetta in Museum Architecture
pins.description: SFMOMA features Mario Botta's 1995 original and Snøhetta's dramatic 2016 expansion — two architectural visions creating one of America's premier modern art museums. #architecture #sanfrancisco #sf #sfmoma #museum #contemporary #snohetta

pins.title: Ferry Building — Beaux-Arts Landmark on the Embarcadero
pins.description: The Ferry Building (1898) with its iconic clock tower is a Beaux-Arts gem on the Embarcadero, now home to San Francisco's beloved artisan marketplace. #architecture #sanfrancisco #sf #beauxarts #ferrybuilding #embarcadero #landmark

pins.title: Salesforce Tower — San Francisco's Tallest Building
pins.description: The Salesforce Tower (2018) by César Pelli rises 1,070 feet with a public art crown installation. San Francisco's tallest building and a new skyline icon. #architecture #sanfrancisco #sf #salesforcetower #skyscraper #contemporary #cesarpelli

pins.title: Coit Tower — Art Deco Tower on Telegraph Hill
pins.description: Coit Tower (1933) crowns Telegraph Hill with Art Deco elegance and Depression-era murals inside. Panoramic views of San Francisco Bay from this beloved landmark. #architecture #sanfrancisco #sf #artdeco #coittower #telegraphhill #landmark

pins.title: Palace of Fine Arts — Romanesque Rotunda from the 1915 Exposition
pins.description: The Palace of Fine Arts by Bernard Maybeck (1915) is a breathtaking Romanesque rotunda — the sole survivor of the Panama-Pacific Exposition in the Marina District. #architecture #sanfrancisco #sf #romanesque #palaceoffinearts #maybeck #marina

pins.title: San Francisco City Hall — Beaux-Arts Dome Taller Than the Capitol
pins.description: SF City Hall (1915) by Arthur Brown Jr. features a dome taller than the U.S. Capitol. A Beaux-Arts masterpiece at the heart of the Civic Center. #architecture #sanfrancisco #sf #beauxarts #cityhall #civiccenter #dome

pins.title: Washington National Cathedral — Gothic Revival Masterpiece
pins.description: Washington National Cathedral on Cathedral Ave NW is one of America's greatest Gothic Revival buildings, with soaring spires and stunning stained glass. #architecture #washingtondc #dc #gothicrevival #cathedral #nationalcathedral

pins.title: United States Capitol — Symbol of American Democracy
pins.description: The U.S. Capitol with its iconic cast-iron dome is the centerpiece of Washington DC's monumental architecture and a symbol of American democratic governance. #architecture #washingtondc #dc #neoclassical #capitol #democracy #landmark

pins.title: Hirshhorn Museum — Brutalist Sculpture Garden on the National Mall
pins.description: The Hirshhorn Museum (1974) by Gordon Bunshaft is a bold cylindrical Brutalist building on the National Mall housing modern and contemporary art. #architecture #washingtondc #dc #brutalism #hirshhorn #museum #nationalmall
